services:
AGM Renovations offers Complete basement and Bathroom renovations packages from the professional design through the professional cleaning including:

Drywall- We employ only professional drywall installers and our goal is deliver complete satisfaction to each and every client with the quality of our workmanship and our prompt, reliable service.
    
Taping- Our drywall taping techniques will bring a high quality smooth finish, with a level of excellence you will take pride in.

Painting- We include all wall priming, painting of ceilings, baseboards, casing, crown and cove moldings into our basement construction packages
    
High Grade Laminate Flooring- is standard in our basement renovations packages.

Tiling- Shower, bathroom, or kitchenette tiling will be done by professional tile installers who are employed directly by AGM. A 2 year unlimited warranty is provided to you standard when you finish your basement with AGM
   
Plumbing- Our licensed plumbers will ensure that no problem is left unsolved and you can be sure that any drain or other plumbing defects left by the original house builder will be fixed effectively.

Electrical- We are committed to providing fully licensed electrician service as part of our standard package. Should you ever require an electrical certificate when you decide to sell your property, we will be happy to provide it to you

profile:
Habitat for Humanity Niagara’s ReStore sells new and gently used renovation materials and supplies.

Everything sold in the ReStore has been donated by companies and individuals who want to help Habitat for Humanity meet its goal of eliminating poverty housing in Niagara. That is how we are able to sell everything for at least 50% off retail, or more.  We constantly receive new inventory from a variety of generous supporters, so every trip to the ReStore offers a unique opportunity to discover a fantastic deal, a one-of-a-kind gem or the missing item in your otherwise perfect design.

ReStore profits are applied to reducing the overhead costs of operating Habitat for Humanity Niagara. By covering our own costs, we will be able to direct every dollar donated to our organization to home building.
service_area: Niagara Region - St. Catharines, Niagara Falls, NOTL, Welland, Lincoln, Pelham, West Lincoln, Fort Erie, Port Colborne
products:
We have amazing items, from our salvages, manufactures' overruns, contractors' excess and personal donations from renovations.

At our ReStore you can find appliances, cabinets, doors, electrical, heating, housewares, kitchen & bathroom cabinets, lighting, fasteners & adhesives, paints & tiles, plumbing, toilets, sinks and tubs, trim & lumber, windows and so much more.

All items are priced at 50% off retail or better.  We encourage you to shop often as our inventory is constantly changing.  Be prepared to Cash'n Carry so you won't be disappointed.
services:
Kitchen Salvage Crew:
Our Salvage Crew will come to your home and remove your old kitchen to make room for your renovation. We will work with your construction timetable and it can be arranged to remove your old kitchen the same day as your new one will be installed. Because our intention is to re-sell the items, they are removed with care. Our trained team will grommet electrical lines and cap all plumbing when removing appliances.

The Benefits of using our crew:
Saves you $600-$800 in disposal fees.
Receive a CRA tax receipt for your donation when your kitchen is sold. 
Help protect the environment by saving useable materials from ending up in landfill. 
Proceeds from the sale of your kitchen help support Habitat for Humanity Niagara
